Through each book we also witness Yui growing less and less resistant to Leo’s love so it is my hope they will eventually end up together and fix each other.

Explanation (spoilers): Yui, the main character in the series, suffered from domestic abuse when she was young. She and her brother turned to each other to look for warmth, which is also implied in the story that they began an incestuous relationship as children. But around 20 years prior to the first story in the series, her brother died. She pretty much was left broken after that. She wears mask because there are scars across her face left there when she attempted suicide (There’re also scars on her wrist). She’s fucked up, depressed, sex-addicted, suicidal, pessimistic, and a mess in general. Leo, the male main character in this series, is also fucked up (less than she is). He is in love with her fully knowing that she cannot reciprocate the feelings since the only one she romantically loved died 20 years ago and she still hasn’t walked out of it. Leo consistently finds girlfriends to forget Yui but comes back to her every time.
